features: Pay Great Attention to safety: Irontar bathroom freestanding cabinet is equipped with anti-toppling fitting to protect the safety of your family. If you accidentally pull the drawer vigorously, don't worry, there is a built-in drawer stopper to prevent the drawer from falling

Multifunctional: Not only bathroom cabinet, perfect as storage floor cabinet, chest of drawers or sideboard, white is an easy color to match, making it suitable to be placed in bathroom, living room, kitchen, entryway or anywhere you want

Sturdy & Stable: Made of high-quality EPA-grade particleboard and MDF, the structure isn't easy to shake, plus we added many reinforcements around the edges to maintain integrity and strength of the freestanding cabinet, so don't worry about stability
Easy to Install: It's easy to put together with detailed, step-by-step assembly instructions and numbered accessories, just taking about 40 minutes, you can get a practical storage cabinet

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 16, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Cracked and broken
reviews.reviewText: Several pieces came cracked and corners broken off. A few pieces came dirty/dusty like. Maybe sitting awhile before being boxed? Definitely not what I expected.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Product for Small houses
reviews.reviewText: I bought this because I needed extra space to store personal hygiene products in my small apartment. Once I was able to assemble it was great but the instructions are not the best in the beginning or maybe I just can't understand them if the item has too many pieces LOL. So far it has serve its purpose and seems sturdy.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Decent if you understand what you’re getting
reviews.reviewText: I bought this as extra bathroom storage, so it’s a decent piece for that purpose. I don’t think I’d want this piece in my living room, dining room, etc. because it definitely looks like mdf board. It’s not IKEA quality. I am a pretty handy person and have assembled a lot of furniture. I had a cordless drill and multiple screwdrivers ready. This tiny cabinet took forever to assemble, and I was moving quickly. So, if you are assembling it alone, be prepared for a solid two hours. The pieces holding the back in place were a huge pain, but otherwise, everything went together as intended with no missing pieces or split boards. Overall, I’m happy because it looks nice for what it is. But, considering how long it takes to assemble, I don’t think the price is a “deal.”

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Exactly as pictured and described
reviews.reviewText: While the assembly took a while and had many steps, the graphic instructions were spot on and helpful. Each piece was clearly marked. Everything assembled as intended and the unit is square and straight. It came well packaged. It looks very cute and fits exactly as I need it to. Would buy again (if I needed another one.)

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Some screws are too long and it has a bad smell
reviews.reviewText: Assembly instructions were in a different language but the pictures were easy to follow. A few of the screws were too long (yes I used the correct screws according to the instructions) and it screwed through the surfaces. One surface was the inside where the door magnet is secured and the other was the very top surface where the screw secure the front molding. So I currently have 2 screw punctures at the top surface. I have the piece in my master bathroom and it release a somewhat toxic strange smell through my bathroom and bedroom causing my household members a headache when they entered my room. I left in the garage for now hoping it will air out.
